\setline{27}\linenumannotation{c}\edtext{śaṅkhinīnālaṃ}{\Bfootnote{em. : \textit{śaṃkhinīnāla} Ms}} saṃprāpya \linenumannotation{d}\edtext{cātiśūnyaṃ}{\Bfootnote{em. BIRCH : \textit{cāsthiśūnyaṃ} Ms}{\Cfootnote{Vgl. As 20.7\textsuperscript{a-d}: saṃpūrṇāyāṃ dvitīyāyām atiśūnyaṃ prajāyate | bherīśabdastadāmadhyevipākakṣaṇasaṃbhavaḥ ||7|| Belegt die Verwendung des Begriffes \textit{ātiśūnya} im Kontext des \textit{Amṛtasiddhi}.}}} bibharti saḥ ||27||\&


